{
  "stem": "7458.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] As soon as we released, we immediately ran back to the woods and we found my father still alive in the creek.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We brought him home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We paid a neighbor, Bolke, who lived across the street from us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "His daughter went to the next town, [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Kinochien ?], where there was a drug store, to get some medicine.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We nursed him back to life.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "He begged us to let him die, but we didn't.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We nursed him back to life.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] since-- since most of the Jewish homes were burned, the Jews had no homes to go to.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So each family that still had a home took in several other families.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I believe my parents took in four other families.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So there were over 30 people living in our house.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And from that day on, the actual Holocaust became a daily reality, and it was sheer hell.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Every few days, the Germans would drive into town, round up, usually, some young men to do a certain job, like snow plowing or snow cleaning.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They would make them work for a day or two.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Then make them dig a hole, line them up, and shoot them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Anybody who was taken for a day's work or two day's work never got back unless they managed to escape, through some miracle.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The Polish neighbors were as bad as the Germans.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "In some cases, worse.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "They formed police that helped the Germans, and they did horrible things.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "They would make terrible demands on us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "They would-- they eventually they set up a Commissar, a German who supervised.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And the Jews had to build a new home for the Commissar.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
